CSS CHALLENGE REQUIREMENTS:


Here are the requirements:

1. Font - Use the `Lato` font from Google Fonts. Add the correct link to the head of the HTML file and the correct 
    font-family to the body.    DONE

2. Body - Make body font size `18px` and a line height of` 1.6`.    DONE

3. Header - Make the header background color `#5e175b` and the text color white in hexidecimal format (Short version).  DONE

4. Header H1 - Align text to `center`, font size `40px` and a text indent of `20px`.    DONE

5. Anchor Tags - Remove the underline from all anchor tags and give them a color of `#333`. 
When hovered over, change the color to `rebeccapurple`. Make the active color `red`.    DONE

6. UL - Set the list style type to `none` and give the list a padding of `0`. I know we have not gone over padding yet. 
    It is `padding: 0`. DONE

7. Main Menu - Give the main menu a background color of `#f4f4f4`. Make it all uppercase using the `text-transform` 
    property and text indent of `10px`. DONE

8. Lead Paragraph - Make the font `bold`, a size of `20px` and the color `rebeccapurple`.   DONE
